Resident Engineer
03 May 2014 06:44 AM - UAE
.
WSP in the Middle East has a number of exciting opportunities to join the Supervision team on major projects throughout the UAE.The Resident Engineer has responsibility for organising the day to day supervision of the Contractors operations and ensuring that the works are constructed in accordance with the specification and drawings.
Responsibilities
To lead a multi-disciplinary site based team generally comprising of but not limited to.• Construction Planning• Quantity Surveying • Architectural• Structural Engineering• Mechanical Engineering• Public Health• Transportation• Health & SafetyTo oversee Site Construction Supervision Services generally comprising of the following;• Contract Administration including acting as the Engineer under FIDIC• Coordination and liaison with the design teamManagement of the site technical team overseeing;• Contractors submittals• Managing the quality of the construction• Monitoring progress on site Contract Administration including issuing instructions, cost management, reviewing contractors claims• Preparation of reports to the employer
Requirements
Degree educated with minimum of 15 years' experience in undertaking the role of a Resident Engineer, 5 years of which shall have been within the Middle East on large multi-disciplinary projects The role will require the excellent communication skills for the production of reports and chairing of meetings.You shall be familiar with a tight programme situation, used to dealing with potential claims, and ideally from a structures background. The ro (more...)
